author: {'id': 1093897077, 'name': 'Colleen Cimini'}
body:
DANBURY, Conn. - Sept. 28, 2023 - PRLog -- BauerFinancial, Inc., the Nation's Premier Bank Rating Firm, is pleased to announce that Savings
Bank of Danbury has earned its top (5-Star) rating for financial strength and stability. This marks Savings Bank of Danbury's 135th consecutive quarter for receiving Bauer's recommendation (5-Stars or 4-Stars). This latest rating was assigned in September 2023 based on June 30, 2023 financial data and signifies that Savings Bank of Danbury is among the strongest banks in the nation.
 Bauer rates every federally-insured U.S. chartered bank with the same strict standards, and is honored to report that Savings Bank of Danbury has earned its 5-Star rating. "As a community bank, Savings Bank of Danbury keeps its focus on consumers, small businesses and the community at hand", remarks Karen Dorway, President of BauerFinancial. "The employees of Savings Bank of Danbury are invested in the community. They volunteer their time and talent with area non-profit organizations and at many community events. Savings Bank of Danbury supports their efforts and together they contribute to making the area a great place to bank, live and work."
 "We are pleased to receive this professional endorsement of our stability and success from BauerFinancial," said Martin G. Morgado, President and CEO of Savings Bank of Danbury. "The commitment to excellence from our Board of Directors to our employees is reflected in this top rating. We are proud of our record and our service to the community."
 Savings Bank of Danbury has been a dedicated banking partner for the community for 174 years. Making connections and supporting the community has been its hallmark since inception. Being rated 5-Stars by Bauer shows confidence that Savings Bank of Danbury has the financial strength to continue to do so.
 About Savings Bank of Danbury
 Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion. Savings Bank of Danbury has 16 branch offices in Bethel, Brookfield, Danbury, New Fairfield, New Milford, Newtown, Norwalk, Southbury, Stamford, and Waterbury. Stamford Mortgage Company, a division of Savings Bank of Danbury, has a local office on Summer Street in Stamford. Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community.
 For more information about Savings Bank of Danbury, visit www.SBDanbury.com
 Contact
 Colleen Cimini
 ***@prfirst.com
 End

Bauer rates every federally-insured U.S. chartered bank with the same strict standards, and is honored to report that Savings Bank of Danbury has earned its 5-Star rating. “As a community bank, Savings Bank of Danbury keeps its focus on consumers, small businesses and the community at hand”, remarks Karen Dorway, President of BauerFinancial. “The employees of Savings Bank of Danbury are invested in the community. They volunteer their time and talent with area non-profit organizations and at many community events. Savings Bank of Danbury supports their efforts and together they contribute to making the area a great place to bank, live and work.” “We are pleased to receive this professional endorsement of our stability and success from BauerFinancial,” said Martin G. Morgado, President and CEO of Savings Bank of Danbury. “The commitment to excellence from our Board of Directors to our employees is reflected in this top rating. We are proud of our record and our service to the community.”

Savings Bank of Danbury has been a dedicated banking partner for the community for 174 years. Making connections and supporting the community has been its hallmark since inception. Being rated 5-Stars by Bauer shows confidence that Savings Bank of Danbury has the financial strength to continue to do so. About Savings Bank of Danbury

Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion. Savings Bank of Danbury has 16 branch offices in Bethel, Brookfield, Danbury, New Fairfield, New Milford, Newtown, Norwalk, Southbury, Stamford, and Waterbury. Stamford Mortgage Company, a division of Savings Bank of Danbury, has a local office on Summer Street in Stamford. Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community. For more information about Savings Bank of Danbury, visit www.SBDanbury.com

Bank and Credit Union data compiled from financial data for the period noted, as reported to federal regulators. The financial data obtained from these sources is consistently reliable, although; the accuracy and completeness of the data cannot be guaranteed by BauerFinancial, Inc. Since 1983, BauerFinancial has relied upon this data in its judgment and in rendering its opinion (e.g. determination of star ratings). BauerFinancial, Inc. is not a financial advisor; it is an independent bank research firm. No institution can pay for or opt out of a BauerFinancial rating. Star-ratings are all available for free at bauerfinancial.com. ###

body:
The Savings Bank of Danbury will host a First Time Home Buyer’s Seminar on Thursday, September 28, 2023 from 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. at the Latinos for Educational Advocacy and Diversity (LEAD) Community Center, 358 Main Street in Danbury, CT. The seminar will be presented in Spanish.

The event is free and open to the public. The event presenter will be Yadiry Rodriguez, Savings Bank of Danbury, Mortgage Originator. Topics discussed will include programs available for first time homebuyers, how much is needed for downpayment and closing expenses, and how to get started with pre-approval. Individuals may RSVP by email at marketing@sbdanbury.com or on Eventbrite. All attendees will receive $500 off the closing costs for first time homebuyer purchase.

Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion. Savings Bank of Danbury has 16 branch offices in Bethel, Brookfield, Danbury, New Fairfield, New Milford, Newtown, Norwalk, Southbury, Stamford, and Waterbury. Stamford Mortgage Company, a division of Savings Bank of Danbury, has a local office on Summer Street in Stamford. Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community.

For more information about Savings Bank of Danbury, visit www.SBDanbury.com

author: {'id': 1093897077, 'name': 'Colleen Cimini'}
body:
Highest rating given for Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) compliance
DANBURY, Conn. - Aug. 4, 2023 - PRLog --
 Savings Bank of Danbury (http://sbdanbury.com) has received an "Outstanding" rating from the Federal Deposit Insurance Commission (FDIC) for its compliance with the Community Reinvestment Act (CRA).
 The FDIC released its list today, detailing the specific ratings that it assigned to banks across the nation earlier this year.
 The Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) was enacted in 1977 and encourages banks and savings associations to help meet the credit needs of all segments of their communities, including low- and moderate-income neighborhoods and individuals. CRA applies to FDIC-insured depository institutions, such as national banks, savings associations, and state-chartered commercial and savings banks.
 Regulators assess the record of each bank in fulfilling its obligation to the community and consider that record in evaluating and approving applications for charters, bank mergers, acquisitions, and branch openings. A bank is evaluated on its record of helping meet the credit needs of its entire community, including low- and moderate-income neighborhoods, consistent with safe and sound operations.
 Martin G. Morgado, President and Chief Executive Officer at Savings Bank of Danbury, said, "We are very pleased to once again receive a rating of 'Outstanding' from the FDIC regarding Community Reinvestment Act compliance. For us, meeting and supporting the needs of the communities that we serve has always been a top priority, and will continue to be so going forward."
 About Savings Bank of Danbury
 Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion. Savings Bank of Danbury has 16 branch offices in Bethel, Brookfield, Danbury, New Fairfield, New Milford, Newtown, Norwalk, Southbury, Stamford, and Waterbury. Stamford Mortgage Company, a division of Savings Bank of Danbury, has a local office on Summer Street in Stamford. Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community.
 For more information about Savings Bank of Danbury, visit www.SBDanbury.com or on Facebook at www.facebook.com/ SBDanbury.
 Contact
 Colleen Cimini
 ***@prfirst.com
 End

DANBURY, Conn. - Aug. 4, 2023 - PRLog --
 Savings Bank of Danbury (http://sbdanbury.com) has received an "Outstanding" rating from the Federal Deposit Insurance Commission (FDIC) for its compliance with the Community Reinvestment Act (CRA).', 'The Community Reinvestment Act (CRA) was enacted in 1977 and encourages banks and savings associations to help meet the credit needs of all segments of their communities, including low- and moderate-income neighborhoods and individuals.', 'Martin G. Morgado, President and Chief Executive Officer at Savings Bank of Danbury, said, "We are very pleased to once again receive a rating of 'Outstanding' from the FDIC regarding Community Reinvestment Act compliance.', '"
 About Savings Bank of Danbury
 Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion.', 'Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community.

title: Savings Bank of Danbury receives "Outstanding" rating from the FDIC

body:
This post was contributed by a community member. The views expressed here are the author's own.

Community Corner Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation Grant Applications Available Non-Profit Organizations can now apply for grant funding. Savings Bank of Danbury Awarded $277,500 to 108 organizations in 2022. Reply

The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation has announced that applications are available for local non-profit agencies to apply for grants with applications due by October 2, 2023.



Applications for the grants are available at the bank’s website at www.SBDanbury.com. The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation (SBD Foundation) is administered by a committee of Savings Bank of Danbury Corporators, directors and bank officers. The grants help support agencies in the areas of Affordable Housing, Arts and Culture, Community Service and Economic Development, Education and Health and Human Service.

The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation awarded $277,500 to 108 organizations in 19 communities in 2022. These grants represent a 15% increase over 2021 grants making this the foundations largest award year to date. The emphasis of the donations was in the areas of food insecurity, housing and mental health. In 2004, the Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation was established to support local non-profit agencies that reflect the core values of the Bank. The Foundation provides grants to support a wide range of initiatives and programs in the areas of Affordable Housing, Arts & Culture, Community Services & Economic Development, Education, and Health & Human Services. Since its establishment, the Foundation has awarded more than $2.75 million to organizations making a positive difference in our communities.

The Savings Bank of Danbury is proud of our commitment to provide financial support to organizations vital to the well-being, growth and prosperity in the communities we serve.” said Stacy Singer, Assistant Vice President and Community Development Officer of Savings Bank of Danbury. “We extend our heartfelt thanks and gratitude to these outstanding agencies, their staff and volunteers. They work tirelessly every day to ensure that our communities are better places to live and work. Individuals and families can reach out to agencies when in need 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.” The Foundation Grants Committee meets once a year to review requests. Awards are made to eligible 501(c)(3) tax-exempt organizations in all of the communities the bank serves. Any organization interested in being considered should review the application's checklist and include all of the elements listed on the application.

About Savings Bank of Danbury Established in 1849 and headquartered at 220 Main Street, Danbury, Savings Bank of Danbury is a mutual savings bank with assets in excess of $1.4 billion. Savings Bank of Danbury has 16 branch offices in Bethel, Brookfield, Danbury, New Fairfield, New Milford, Newtown, Norwalk, Southbury, Stamford, and Waterbury. Stamford Mortgage Company, a division of Savings Bank of Danbury, has a local office on Summer Street in Stamford. Savings Bank of Danbury is committed to serving their community.

title: Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation Grant Applications Available

author: {'id': 3071886}
body:
Published on Tuesday, 25 July 2023 14:40 Written by Colleen Cimini
The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation has announced that applications are available for local non-profit agencies to apply for grants with applications due by October 2, 2023.
 Applications for the grants are available at the bank’s website at www.SBDanbury.com. The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation (SBD Foundation) is administered by a committee of Savings Bank of Danbury Corporators, directors and bank officers.
 The grants help support agencies in the areas of Affordable Housing, Arts and Culture, Community Service and Economic Development, Education and Health and Human Service.
 The Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation awarded $277,500 to 108 organizations in 19 communities in 2022. These grants represent a 15% increase over 2021 grants making this the foundations largest award year to date. The emphasis of the donations was in the areas of food insecurity, housing and mental health.
 In 2004, the Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation was established to support local non-profit agencies that reflect the core values of the Bank. The Foundation provides grants to support a wide range of initiatives and programs in the areas of Affordable Housing, Arts & Culture, Community Services & Economic Development, Education, and Health & Human Services. Since its establishment, the Foundation has awarded more than $2.75 million to organizations making a positive difference in our communities.
 The Savings Bank of Danbury is proud of our commitment to provide financial support to organizations vital to the well-being, growth and prosperity in the communities we serve.” said Stacy Singer, Assistant Vice President and Community Development Officer of Savings Bank of Danbury. “We extend our heartfelt thanks and gratitude to these outstanding agencies, their staff and volunteers. They work tirelessly every day to ensure that our communities are better places to live and work. Individuals and families can reach out to agencies when in need 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.”
 The Foundation Grants Committee meets once a year to review requests. Awards are made to eligible 501(c)(3) tax-exempt organizations in all of the communities the bank serves. Any organization interested in being considered should review the application's checklist and include all of the elements listed on the application.
 For more information about Savings Bank of Danbury, visit www.SBDanbury.com or on Facebook at

title: Savings Bank of Danbury Foundation Grant Applications for Non-Profit Organizations Now Available

author: {'id': 1048542, 'name': 'Phil Hall'}
body:
The Savings Bank of Danbury has named Chad Stewart as first vice president and commercial team leader for the Southern Connecticut region.

In his new job, Stewart will be based at the bank’s Norwalk branch and will lead a team of commercial lenders dedicated to building the deposit and loan portfolio for the Stamford and Norwalk area.

Stewart was most recently a senior vice president and commercial team leader for Connecticut Community Bank based in Westport and first vice president and team leader for First Niagara Bank in Norwalk.

title: New commercial team leader at Savings Bank of Danbury

author: {'id': 4232073, 'name': 'Diane Mclaughlin'}
body:
The Savings Bank of Danbury has hired Chad Stewart as first vice president and commercial team leader for the Southern Connecticut region.
In his new role, Stewart will lead a team of commercial lenders building the deposit and loan portfolio for the Stamford and Norwalk area, the bank said in a statement. He will be based in the bank’s Norwalk branch, which opened last year.  Stewart has 34 years of banking experience. He was most recently a senior vice president and commercial team leader for the Westport branch of Connecticut Community Bank. He also worked at the former First Niagara Bank as a first vice president and team leader.  A member and past president of the Fairfield Rotary Club, Stewart is president of the Fairfield Rotary Foundation and a loan committee member of Capital for Change.  “Chad will lead our team of commercial lenders dedicated to Stamford and Norwalk,” Patrick Kelley, senior vice president of Savings Bank of Danbury, said in the statement. “He brings great experience and knowledge to the team, his expertise and commitment to customer service will bring great value to SBD.”

title: Savings Bank of Danbury Hires Commercial Team Lead for Norwalk

author: {'id': 3083456}
body:
The Savings Bank of Danbury has hired Brian Falkowski as vice president of commercial lending.
Falkowski will focus on building commercial business banking in the Fairfield County and Westchester markets, the bank said in a statement.  Falkowski has 21 years of banking experience, including several managerial positions. Previous employers include Renovo Financial and Webster Bank, according to his LinkedIn profile. Falkowski is a member of the Norwalk Rotary Club, Norwalk Chamber, Fairfield County Commercial Brokers Network, Connected Networking Group and Junior Achievement.  “We will look to Brian to create financing solutions to local business owners with a focus on the Fairfield County and Westchester Market,” Patrick Kelley, senior vice president at Savings Bank of Danbury, said in the statement. “We are pleased to have Brian join our professional team.”

title: Brian Falkowski Joins Savings Bank of Danbury

author: {'id': 1048542, 'name': 'Phil Hall'}
body:
The Savings Bank of Danbury has named Brian R. Falkowski as vice president of commercial lending.

In his new job, Falkowski will focus on building commercial business banking in the Fairfield County and Westchester markets. Prior to joining Savings Bank of Danbury, Falkowski was senior vice president of lending at Renovo Financial LLC. Earlier in his career, he held vice president positions at Webster Bank, First Niagara Bank and HSBC.

“We will look to Brian to create financing solutions to local business owners with a focus on the Fairfield County and Westchester Market,” said Patrick Kelley, senior vice president of Savings Bank of Danbury. “We are pleased to have Brian join our professional team.”
